  "event_preview": "Darlington Raceway is a 1.366-mile (2.198 km) egg-shaped oval in Darlington, South Carolina, nicknamed \"The Lady in Black\" and \"The Track Too Tough to Tame.\" The unique asymmetrical shape — wide and sweeping through Turns 1–2, tight and pinched through Turns 3–4 — arose from a minnow pond the landowner refused to relocate during construction, and to this day makes it nearly impossible to find a setup that works equally well at both ends. Last repaved after the May 2007 meeting, the abrasive surface chews through tyres mercilessly and punishes even the slightest sideways moment. The Goodyear 400 is contested over 293 laps — one of the most celebrated spring dates on the NASCAR Cup calendar, held annually as part of Throwback Weekend. The defending race winner is Denny Hamlin, who capitalised on a late caution to claim his 56th career Cup Series victory in 2025, edging William Byron by 0.597 seconds after a perfectly-executed final pit stop by his Joe Gibbs Racing crew. The all-time qualifying record at Darlington belongs to Hamlin himself — a 28.694 seconds (171.381 mph) pole lap set during the 2025 Cook Out Southern 500 weekend."
}
